description: Dimensions: L (in plane of contact face) 109.5mm; maxEW 47.7mm; max B. 24; H tongue above contact face 0-2.0; matrix: L 75.0; W bl. e. 29.5; Wm (casting) 32.0; D of inside of m. of cg. between contact face 12.7; T base cg. 2.3; D matrix base 7.0; D bl. e. 1.8; EL Pb. cg. 46,Typology: Matrix/castings: double m-m evident at side of cg.; decn. uncertain; sl. spatulate shape to lower bl.; near perp. ledge at bottom mould give flat-ended bl. e.; inside force, or socket of cg. with almost half elliptical cross-sec.; wells seem steep and near straight; top of Pb cg. seems to approximate to matrix end.,Mould: tendency to concave outsloped edges to notches in corners of gate support, creating sharp inside angle: top of toungue convex on outer side, more angular on inner; widely spaced but sym.core prints - virt. elliptical with domed profiles; narrow contact face mainly flat, little part concave below loop; - perhaps leaving small cavity here when mould closed; location - tongue prob. orig. continuous variable ^ to rounded sec. - variable height, disappearing close to end of side walls; outer tip where intact has marked concave sec. with thin almost pointed outer fg. angled upwards.,Outside: olive to black-green patina, scattered pocking/flaking to pale green dry surface, also much textured corr. layer, light green overlying; inside dull dark grey-green matt sur., much flaked to light and pale green dry surface - esp. at edges etc., some also revealing smoother ruddy brown surface.
remarks: PIF (3 cards); AFI; DF(C); SI; CI; SN Oct. 79; Source MV; Cont. Card 1.

composition: Res. Lab XRF determination (on Matrices 1 & 3) did not detect any significant parts for Cu, Sn, As, Pb; The stone would appear to have significant quantities of Fe, Po, Ca, Ti, Si
description: Dimensions: of block per illustration; face kept parallel and perpendicular to plane of drawing in each view; faces 1 & 3 approx. parallel in cross section, converging a little in long section; Wt. 2125.7 g,Matrix 1: internal L 162mm; ext. L 171.5; int. W 52; ext. W 59.5; max. D matrix (intact matrix sur.) 6.2; max D. end 3.8; most of matrix surface smooth, intact, & very gently concave; side walls mainly near & flat standing at 70*; v. slight furrows down length probably tooling marks; patch of surface chipped away - roughened surface, but similar blue-grey colour to rest of matrix; most of surrounding face generally flat with slight modulations - probably intact; lower left corner reduced by damage; depth at wide end fairly consistent, even to tip.,Matrix 2: L 193.5 or 160; max W 49 or ?; max D 3.5; surface of matrix rough pocked, sides ill-defined - one virt. straight, other with central [?sevelling]; broad edge very diffuse - two poss. lines of matrix defined by bevels and pittings (shorter length); narrower end virt. pointed; surrounding face undulates - some almost level with matrix surface; colour similar to black;,Matrix 3: int. L 131.5mm; external L 135.5; int. max. W. 54.5; max D side wall (one side) 8.2; max D. other side wall 3.5; max D broad end 5.5; most of matrix smooth and very gently concave, more-or-less flat across broad end, but actual edge angle rises slightly in centre; angle of one side wall very straight - slight ridge inside - other wall very concave line, slightly bowed in section and at angle of c. 70*; top end - no distinct bevel line - but no end of dam.; 2 or 3 small patches chipped to rough texture - sim. blue-grey col. to rest of matrix; much of surrounding face flat with slight undulation -largely undam. prob.; depression reducing lower left side wall poss. dam. - but not fresher sur.; also facet across lower right tip prob. dam. - irregular surface but not fresher.,Face 4: comparatively irregular; tendency for three furrows on lower parts.,Block: pale bluey/greeny grey surface, patches of rusty brown staining?; odd chips at corners with maroon brown surface - prob. more recent; groove across top end and across right side face of face 3 - both look ancient and probably incidental; bottom end slightly hollowed - not smooth, pocked; top end flat; patch of blackening on angle between faces 2 & 3, some moss adhering plus green staining in parts,Medium Grained Sandstone

description: Dimensions: Length: Matrix 1: 13.7mm; Matrix 2: 107mm,Width: blade Matrix 1: 47mm; blade Matrix 2 41mm; Width mouth Matrix 1: 47mm; Width mouth Matrix 2: 52mm; Width axe face beneath moulding Matrix 1: 32.5mm; Width axe face beneath moulding Matrix 2: 34mm; Width body below loop Matrix 1: 38.5mm; Width body below loop Matrix 2: 42.5mm,Depth moulding Matrix 1: 9.5mm; Depth moulding Matrix 2: 8.5mm,Length ribs Matrix 1: 59mm (below base of moulding); Length ribs Matrix 2 53mm (below base of moulding),Depth matrix at moulding Matrix 1: 22mm; Depth matrix at moulding Matrix 2: 20.5mm,Wedge-shaped block, opposite faces converging; ends flat and also not quite parallel; sides bowed, thin end: two grooves off long edge with smaller notch in between, v. slight groove off either side?; thick end: central groove, other diffuse notches flanking - poss. damage; Matrix 1: marked ledge below slightly splayed moulding; rectangular body section with rib-emphasised corners; 3 straight slightly converging ribs; two loops - one springing from moulding, other from just below; spatulate blade forms towards edge; loop grooves with neat 'V' section; one corner rib continues straight where body expands; ribs 'V' sectioned. Matrix 2: upside down from Matrix 1; ledge under slightly splayed moulding; bowed rectangular body section - sides more splayed; rib-emphasised, or crisp body corners; three parallel ribs, not evenly spaced; loop groove with near 'V' section, springing from just below moulding; body parallel sided for much of axe; ribs 'V' sectioned, and tail away to nothing.

description: Dimensions: max dimension 69.0mm; EL tube possibly full L 43.5; B tube (middle) 24.7; Wt. 186.8g,Typology: craggy lump of bronze incorporating half-melted implements: (1) tube with flanged opening on one side at presumed centre, and tube here a little swollen with rounded ridge encircling and continuing onto flange to give very slightly lentrical shape to opening; edge of flange not a regular shape in profile and pres. broken, but surface more smooth; more intact end of tube with slight expansion to ridge and outer bevelled perimeter; basically amorphous lump protruding from this end, may be part of an original rod-like extension; side opening is blocked just below level of tube surface-apparently continuous casting, no crack apparent. (2) short stretch of curved rod of eye-shaped section; length of 13mm of concave face exposed before swallowed by lump; outer face concealed; outer end very rounded - looks most like runner of casting jet, more elliptical than known fleshhook prongs. (3) 'strip' in edge of lump EL 15mm, T 1.5-2.5 - apparently a little twisted along length W of end exposed on face (1) 7.3. (4) 'strip' - with 3 apparent mouldings on exposed face - parallel; EL 10.8; W 9.5 (5) A few other small projections - more amorphous and uncertain whether parts of object.
remarks: PIF; DF(S); SI; RSO 29/5/79; CI; Rec.: SN Aug. 80; Source: Sb. A.; Sub. Inf.: D.T.D. Clarke, Colchester Mus. 23 May 79; Cont. Card. 1
